  "prompt": "How much money per hour do Uber drivers make in Des Moines? What's the most a person can reasonably make per month?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Uber drivers' earnings can vary significantly based on numerous factors including time of day, demand, bonuses, and tips. In Des Moines specifically, the average hourly earnings for Uber drivers tend to range from $15 to $25 per hour. However, this can fluctuate based on the aforementioned factors.\n\nTo estimate the monthly earnings, let's use the higher end of that range for a more optimistic projection:\n\nIf a driver works full-time (40 hours per week):\n- $25 per hour * 40 hours per week = $1,000 per week\n- $1,000 per week * 4 weeks per month = $4,000 per month\n\nTherefore, the most a person can reasonably make per month, if working full-time at the higher end of earnings, could be around $4,000.\n\nIt\u2019s important to note that these figures are gross earnings and do not take into account expenses such as gas, car maintenance, insurance, or taxes, which can significantly reduce take-home pay. Additionally, various incentives, bonuses, or peak-hour rates could alter this estimate.",
